[metadata]
Name:Daze island-return alternative cost
Goal:Win
Turns:4
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Verify Daze can be cast by returning an Island to its owner's hand rather than paying {1}{U}. Regression for mtg-939 (Return<N/Type> alt-cost path). P0 has 0 mana available but controls an Island; Daze in hand. P1 casts Lightning Bolt at P0. P0 responds by returning the Island (alt-cost) and countering with Daze. P0 life should stay at 20; the Lightning Bolt must be in P1's graveyard (countered); P0 Island must be in P0 hand (returned as cost).

[state]
turn=3
activeplayer=p1
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Daze
p0library=Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains; Plains
p0graveyard=
p0battlefield=Island
p0exile=

p1life=20
p1hand=Lightning Bolt
p1library=Mountain; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain; Mountain
p1graveyard=
p1battlefield=Mountain
p1exile=

[assertions]
# P0 should survive (Lightning Bolt countered by Daze)
me life eq 20
# Lightning Bolt should be countered (in graveyard)
opponent graveyard contains Lightning Bolt
# P0's Island was returned as Daze's cost (now in P0 hand)
me hand contains Island
# Daze itself resolved (countered the bolt), so Daze goes to graveyard
me graveyard contains Daze
